DESCRIPTION:<br><p dir="ltr">INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 625</p><p dir=
 "ltr">SAINT PAUL PUBLIC SCHOOLS</p><br><u>SPECIAL NOTICE FROM THE&nbsp\;<u>
 BOARD OF EDUCATION</u></u><br><br><p dir="ltr">In the Matter of a Closed Me
 eting&nbsp\;Regarding Labor Negotiations&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;
 &nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;</p><p dir="ltr"></p><
 p dir="ltr"><u>____________________________________________________________
 ____________________</u></p><br><p dir="ltr">To:&nbsp\;Directors of the Boa
 rd of Education of Independent School&nbsp\;District No. 625</p><p dir="ltr
 "></p><br><br><p dir="ltr">PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that the undersigned\, purs
 uant to Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, Subdivision 6\, does hereby ca
 ll a special meeting of the Board of Education of Independent School Distri
 ct No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be held and convened on&nbsp\;<
 b>Tuesday\, October 11\, 2022 beginning at 4:30 p.m. in Conference Room 5A 
 of the Administration Building located at 360 Colborne Street</b>\, during 
 which by majority public vote the Board shall move into a closed session to
  consider strategy for labor negotiations\, including negotiation strategie
 s\, developments\, discussion\, and review of labor negotiation proposals f
 or these bargaining units\, including Principals\, PEA\, AFSCME\, Bus Drive
 rs\, CCEA\, and Custodians\, as is provided for by Minnesota Statutes Secti
 on 13D.03.&nbsp\;</p><br><p dir="ltr">Following the closed session\, the Bo
 ard shall continue in open session and\, if necessary\, shall discuss and t
 ake action with respect to labor negotiations.</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p d
 ir="ltr">The Regular Meeting of the Board of Education will follow as sched
 uled in Conference Rooms A and B of 360 Colborne\, beginning at 5:30 p.m. w
 ith Public Comment\, and the start of the Regular Meeting at 6:05 p.m.</p><
 br><br><p dir="ltr">September 15\, 2022</p><br><p dir="ltr">Jim Vue<br>Chai
 r\, Board of Education</p><p dir="ltr">Independent School District No. 625&
 nbsp\;</p>Saint Paul Public Schools
