  of A Series of Special Meetings Regarding Labor Negotiations  </p><p dir="
 ltr"><u></u></p><p dir="ltr"></p><p dir="ltr"><u>__________________________
 ___________________________________________________________</u></p><br><p d
 ir="ltr">To: Directors of the Board of Education of Independent School </p>
 <p dir="ltr">District No. 625</p><br><br><p dir="ltr">PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, 
 that the undersigned\, pursuant to Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, Sub
 division 6\, does hereby call a series of special meetings of the Board of 
 Education of Independent School District No. 625\, Saint Paul Public School
 s\, to be held and convened on:</p><br><ul><li dir="ltr"><b><p dir="ltr">Tu
 esday\, October 24\, 2023</p></b></li><li dir="ltr"><b><p dir="ltr">Tuesday
 \, November 14\, 2023</p></b></li><li dir="ltr"><b><p dir="ltr">Tuesday\, D
 ecember 19\, 2023</p></b></li></ul><br><p dir="ltr"><b>Meetings will commen
 ce at 4:00 p.m. in Conference Room 5A of the Administration Building locate
 d at 360 Colborne Street</b>\, during which by majority public vote the Boa
 rd shall move into a closed session to consider strategy for labor negotiat
 ions\, including negotiation strategies\, developments\, discussion\, and r
 eview of labor negotiation proposals for all bargaining units\, including A
 SAP\, Educational Assistants\, Machinists\, Nutrition Services Personnel\, 
 Principals\, School and Community Service Professionals\, Teachers\, MMSA\,
  PEA\, SPSO\, AFSCME\, Bus Drivers\, CCEA\, Custodians\, Tri-Council\, Bric
 klayers\, Carpenters\, Cement Masons\, Electricians\, Glaziers\, Painters\,
  Pipe fitters\, Plasterers\, Plumbers\, Roofers\, Sheet Metal Workers\, and
  Tri-Council Temps.\, as is provided for by Minnesota Statutes Section 13D.
 03. </p><br><p dir="ltr">Following the closed session\, the Board shall con
 tinue in open session and\, if necessary\, shall discuss and take action wi
 th respect to labor negotiations.</p><br><p dir="ltr">September 22\, 2023</
 p><br><p dir="ltr">Jim Vue<br>Chair\, Board of Education</p><p dir="ltr">In
 dependent School District No. 625 </p>Saint Paul Public Schools
