DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 625</p><p dir="ltr
 ">SAINT PAUL PUBLIC SCHOOLS</p><br><u>SPECIAL NOTICE FROM THE&nbsp\;<u>BOAR
 D OF EDUCATION</u></u><br><br><br><br>In the Matter of A Series of Special 
 Meetings&nbsp\;Regarding Labor Negotiations<br><br><p dir="ltr">To:&nbsp\;D
 irectors of the Board of Education of Independent School&nbsp\;District No.
  625</p><p dir="ltr">PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that the undersigned\, pursuant t
 o Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, Subdivision 6\, does hereby call a s
 eries of special meetings of the Board of Education of Independent School D
 istrict No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be held and convened on:</
 p><br><ul><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Friday\, March 4\, 2022&nbsp\;</p></li
 ><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Saturday\, March 5\, 2022 at 1:00 p.m.&nbsp\;</
 p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Sunday\, March 6\, 2022 at 1:00 p.m.&nbsp
 \;</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Monday\, March 7\, 2022</p></li><li d
 ir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Tuesday\, March 8\, 2022 at 3:30 p.m.</p></li><li dir
 ="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Wednesday\, March 9\, 2022</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir
 ="ltr">Thursday\, March 10\, 2022</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Friday
 \, March 11\, 2022</p></li></ul><br><p dir="ltr"><b>Meetings will commence 
 at 4:30 p.m.\, unless otherwise noted\, in Conference Room 5B of the Admini
 stration Building located at 360 Colborne Street</b>\, during which by majo
 rity public vote the Board shall move into a closed session to consider str
 ategy for labor negotiations\, including negotiation strategies\, developme
 nts\, discussion\, and review of labor negotiation proposals for all bargai
 ning units\, including ASAP\, Educational Assistants\, Machinists\, Nutriti
 on Services Personnel\, Principals\, School and Community Service Professio
 nals\, Teachers\, MMSA\, PEA\, SPSO\, AFSCME\, Bus Drivers\, CCEA\, Custodi
 ans\, Tri-Council\, Bricklayers\, Carpenters\, Cement Masons\, Electricians
 \, Glaziers\, Painters\, Pipe fitters\, Plasterers\, Plumbers\, Roofers\, S
 heet Metal Workers\, and Tri-Council Temps.\, as is provided for by Minneso
 ta Statutes Section 13D.03.&nbsp\;</p><br><p dir="ltr">Following the closed
  session\, the Board shall continue in open session and\, if necessary\, sh
 all discuss and take action with respect to labor negotiations.</p><br><br>
 <p dir="ltr">February 28\, 2022</p><br><p dir="ltr">Jim Vue<br>Chair\, Boar
 d of Education</p><p dir="ltr">Independent School District No. 625&nbsp\;</
 p><p dir="ltr">Saint Paul Public Schools</p>
