DESCRIPTION:<b><p>INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 625</p><p>SAINT PAUL PUBL
 IC SCHOOLS</p><br><b><br></b></b>SPECIAL NOTICE FROM THE BOARD OF EDUCATION
 <b><br><br><p>In the Matter of A Series of Closed Meetings&nbsp\;</p><p>Reg
 arding Labor Negotiations&nbsp\;</p><p></p><p>_____________________________
 ________________________________________________________</p><br><p>To:Direc
 tors of the Board of Education of Independent School&nbsp\;</p><p>District 
 No. 625</p><br><br><p>PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that the undersigned\, pursuant 
 to Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, Subdivision 6\, does hereby call a 
 series of special meetings of the Board of Education of Independent School 
 District No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be held and convened on:<
 /p><ul><li><p>Thursday\, January 20\, 2022 at 5:00 p.m.</p></li><li><p>Mond
 ay\, January 24\, 2022</p></li><li><p>Monday\, February 7\, 2022</p></li><l
 i><p>Monday\, February 21\, 2022</p></li><li><p>Monday\, March 7\, 2022</p>
 </li><li><p>Monday\, March 21\, 2022</p></li><li><p>Monday\, April 4\, 2022
 </p></li><li><p>Monday\, April 18\, 2022</p></li></ul><br><p>Meetings will 
 commence at 4:30 p.m.\, unless otherwise noted\, in Conference Room 5A of t
 he Administration Building located at 360 Colborne Street\, during which by
  majority public vote the Board shall move into a closed session to conside
 r strategy for labor negotiations\, including negotiation strategies\, deve
 lopments\, discussion\, and review of labor negotiation proposals for all b
 argaining units\, including ASAP\, Educational Assistants\, Machinists\, Nu
 trition Services Personnel\, Principals\, School and Community Service Prof
 essionals\, Teachers\, MMSA\, PEA\, SPSO\, AFSCME\, Bus Drivers\, CCEA\, Cu
 stodians\, Tri-Council\, Bricklayers\, Carpenters\, Cement Masons\, Electri
 cians\, Glaziers\, Painters\, Pipe fitters\, Plasterers\, Plumbers\, Roofer
 s\, Sheet Metal Workers\, and Tri-Council Temps.\, as is provided for by Mi
 nnesota Statutes Section 13D.03.&nbsp\;</p><br><p>Following the closed sess
 ion\, the Board shall continue in open session and\, if necessary\, shall d
 iscuss and take action with respect to labor negotiations.</p><br><br><p>Ja
 nuary 13\, 2022</p><br><p>Jim Vue<br>Chair\, Board of Education</p><p>Indep
 endent School District No. 625&nbsp\;</p>Saint Paul Public Schools</b>
