 SCHOOLS</p><p>SPECIAL NOTICE FROM THE BOARD OF EDUCATION<br><br></p><p>In t
 he Matter of a Closed Meeting Regarding Labor Negotiations   </p><p>_______
 _____________________________________________________________________</p><p
 > </p><p>To: Directors of the Board of Education of Independent School </p>
 <p>District No. 625</p><p><br><br></p><p>PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that the unde
 rsigned\, pursuant to Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, Subdivision 6\, 
 does hereby call a series of special meetings of the Board of Education of 
 Independent School District No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be hel
 d and convened on:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Wednesday\, May 10\, 2023</strong>
 </p></li><li><p><strong>Thursday\, June 1\, 2023</strong></p></li></ul><p><
 strong>Meetings will begin at 4:30 p.m. in Conference Room 5A of the Admini
 stration Building located at 360 Colborne Street</strong>\, during which by
  majority public vote the Board shall move into a closed session to conside
 r strategy for labor negotiations\, including negotiation strategies\, deve
 lopments\, discussion\, and review of labor negotiation proposals for all b
 argaining units including ASAP\, Educational Assistants\, Machinists\, Nutr
 ition Services Personnel\, Principals\, School and Community Service Profes
 sionals\, Teachers\, MMSA\, PEA\, SPSO\, AFSCME\, Bus Drivers\, CCEA\, Cust
 odians\, Tri-Council\, Bricklayers\, Carpenters\, Cement Masons\, Electrici
 ans\, Glaziers\, Painters\, Pipe fitters\, Plasterers\, Plumbers\, Roofers\
 , Sheet Metal Workers\, and Tri-Council Temps.\, as is provided for by Minn
 esota Statutes Section 13D.03.</p><p>Following the closed session\, the Boa
 rd shall continue in open session and\, if necessary\, shall discuss and ta
 ke action with respect to labor negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>May 4\, 2022</p
 ><p>Jim Vue<br>Chair\, Board of Education</p><p>Independent School District
  No. 625 </p><p>Saint Paul Public Schools</p>
