 BOARD OF EDUCATION</u></u><br><u><u><br></u></u><br><p dir="ltr">In the Mat
 ter of A Series of Closed Meetings<u></u></p><p dir="ltr">Regarding Labor N
 egotiations&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<u></u></p><p dir="ltr"></p><p dir="ltr"><u>______
 ___________________________________________________________________________
 ____</u></p><br><p dir="ltr">To:&nbsp\;Directors of the Board of Education 
 of Independent School&nbsp\;</p><p dir="ltr">District No. 625</p><br><br><p
  dir="ltr">PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that the undersigned\, pursuant to Minnesot
 a Statutes Section 123B.09\, Subdivision 6\, does hereby call a series of s
 pecial meetings of the Board of Education of Independent School District No
 . 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be held and convened on:</p><br><ul>
 <li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Monday\, May 2\, 2022</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p d
 ir="ltr">Monday\, May 16\, 2022</p></li></ul><br><p dir="ltr"><b>Meetings w
 ill commence at 4:30 p.m.\, unless otherwise noted\, in Conference Room 5A 
 of the Administration Building located at 360 Colborne Street</b>\, during 
 which by majority public vote the Board shall move into a closed session to
  consider strategy for labor negotiations\, including negotiation strategie
 s\, developments\, discussion\, and review of labor negotiation proposals f
 or these bargaining units\, including Principals\, MMSA\, PEA\, SPSO\, AFSC
 ME\, Bus Drivers\, CCEA\, Custodians\, Tri-Council\, Bricklayers\, Carpente
 rs\, Cement Masons\, Electricians\, Glaziers\, Painters\, Pipe fitters\, Pl
 asterers\, Plumbers\, Roofers\, Sheet Metal Workers\, and Tri-Council Temps
 .\, as is provided for by Minnesota Statutes Section 13D.03.&nbsp\;</p><br>
 <p dir="ltr">Following the closed session\, the Board shall continue in ope
 n session and\, if necessary\, shall discuss and take action with respect t
 o labor negotiations.</p><br><br><p dir="ltr">April 25\, 2022</p><br><p dir
 ="ltr">Jim Vue<br>Chair\, Board of Education</p><p dir="ltr">Independent Sc
 hool District No. 625&nbsp\;</p>Saint Paul Public Schools
