DESCRIPTION:<br>INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 625<br>SAINT PAUL PUBLIC SC
 HOOLS<br> <br> <br><u>SPECIAL NOTICE FROM THE BOARD OF EDUCATION</u><br><br
 >In the Matter of Listening Session Regarding the FY26 Budget              
                                  <br><u>___________________________________
 __________________________________</u><br><br><br><b>PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, t
 </b>hat the undersigned\, pursuant to Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, 
 Subdivision 6\, does hereby call a Special Meeting of the Board of Educatio
 n of Independent School District No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to b
 e held and convened on<b> Tuesday\, April 29\, 2025 beginning at 5:30 p.m. 
 in Conference Rooms A and B of the District Administration Building located
  at 360 Colborne Street\, Saint Paul\, MN 55102.</b><br><b><br></b><br>The 
 purpose of this meeting is to bring SPPS community members together to offe
 r feedback on the topic of the FY26 budget and future budget cycles. The me
 eting will include a 30-minute budget presentation followed by public comme
 nt.<br><br>The Board will listen to and take notes on every comment and add
 ress what they heard at the Committee of the Board meeting on May 6. Please
  note that comments may not impact the FY26 budget\, but are valuable to th
 e Board and district leaders for future planning. There will be additional 
 opportunities to engage in the next budget cycle (fiscal year 2026-27) begi
 nning in fall 2025.<br><br>Those wishing to provide comments regarding the 
 FY26 Budget may sign up in advance using the District’s form for submitting
  public comment at <a href="www.spps.org/boe">www.spps.org/boe</a> or by e-
 mailing or calling the Board Secretary (sarah.dahlke@spps.org / 651-767-814
 9). <b>Attendees can also sign up in person until 6:30 p.m. on April 29\, 2
 025</b>. <b>Interpreters are available and must be requested in advance via
  the sign-up form.</b><br><br>Individuals providing comments are asked to s
 peak for a maximum of three minutes.<br><br>The meeting is open to all. The
  public may monitor the meeting via live stream at spps.eduvision.tv/LiveSc
 hed.aspx.<br><br>April 17\, 2025<br> <br>                                  
                           Halla Henderson<br>                              
                               Chair\, Board of Education<br>               
                                              Independent School District No
 . 625<br>                                                            Saint 
 Paul Public Schools
LAST-MODIFIED:20250417T164254Z
LOCATION:360 Colborne Street
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Special Meeting of the Board of Education
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
