DESCRIPTION:<br><p>INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 625&nbsp\;</p><br><p>SAI
 NT PAUL PUBLIC SCHOOLS&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>NOTICE OF EMERGENCY MEET
 ING&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><br><p>OF THE BOARD OF EDUCATION&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><br>
 <p>TO BE HELD VIA TELEPHONIC PHONE CONFERENCE&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>T
 o: Directors of the Board of Education of Independent School District No. 6
 25&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that the undersigned\, 
 pursuant to Minnesota Statutes\, Section 13D.04\,&nbsp\;subd. 3 and the cur
 rent state of emergency due to the COVID-19 pandemic\, does hereby call an 
 emergency meeting of the Board of Education of Independent School District 
 No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be held and convened on&nbsp\;Thur
 sday\, March 19\, 2020 at 5:00 pm. Also\, please take notice\, that the und
 ersigned has determined that because of the current state of emergency due 
 to the COVID-19 pandemic\, this meeting will be conducted via a telephonic 
 phone conference pursuant to and in accordance with Minnesota Statutes\, Se
 ction 13D.021.&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>Consistent with current state an
 d federal pandemic guidance\, the undersigned has determined that\, due to 
 the health pandemic and emergency declaration\, a meeting format allowing f
 or open in-person attendance is not practical or prudent. As a result\, it 
 is unfeasible for at least one Board Member\, the Superintendent\, or Gener
 al Counsel to be physically present at the regular meeting location. It is 
 also not feasible for members of the public to attend at the regular meetin
 g location. The School District has set up a conference call telephone numb
 er for members of the public who wish to monitor the emergency school board
  meeting on&nbsp\;March 19\, 2020 at 5:00 pm. Individuals wishing to monito
 r the meeting should dial&nbsp\;651-728-5389&nbsp\;at 5:00 pm and enter the
  meeting code&nbsp\;719 165 833#.&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>At the emerge
 ncy meeting\, the Board:&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>1. Will receive a repo
 rt from the Superintendent on the School District’s implementation of the G
 overnor’s Executive Order of March 15\,&nbsp\;2020\;&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><
 br><p>2. Discuss and establish the process for conducting future meetings o
 f the Board of Education via telephonic phone conference during the current
  state of&nbsp\;emergency\;&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>3. Discuss and esta
 blish alternative processes for receiving public comment when Board of Educ
 ation meetings are held via telephonic phone conference.&nbsp\;</p><br><p><
 /p><br><p>Dated: March 18\, 2020.&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p></p><br><p>Ch
 air\, Board of Education&nbsp\;</p><br><p>Independent School District No. 6
 25&nbsp\;</p><br><p>Saint Paul Public Schools&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200318T214738Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MTG | Emergency Meeting of the Board of Education
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
