DESCRIPTION:<br><p dir="ltr">INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. 625</p><p dir=
 "ltr">SAINT PAUL PUBLIC SCHOOLS</p><br><br><u>NOTICE OF SPECIAL MEETING<u>O
 F THE BOARD OF EDUCATION</u></u><br><p dir="ltr">In the Matter of Listening
  SessionRegarding School Safety</p><p dir="ltr"><u></u></p><p dir="ltr"><u>
 </u></p><p dir="ltr"></p><p dir="ltr"><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u
 ></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p 
 dir="ltr">To: Directors of the Board of Education of Independent School</p>
 <p dir="ltr">District No. 625</p><br><br><p dir="ltr">PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, 
 that the undersigned\, pursuant to Minnesota Statutes Section 123B.09\, Sub
 division 6\, does hereby call a Special Meeting of the Board of Education o
 f Independent School District No. 625\, Saint Paul Public Schools\, to be h
 eld and convened on <b>Tuesday\, February 28\, 2023 beginning at 4:30 p.m. 
 at the Great Hall at Washington Technology Magnet School located at 1495 Ri
 ce Street\, Saint Paul\, MN 55117.</b></p><br><p dir="ltr">The purpose of t
 his meeting is to bring SPPS community members together to offer recommenda
 tions on the topic of school safety.</p><br><p dir="ltr">The information ga
 thered at this meeting will be used to help inform potential solutions to i
 mprove school safety. Additional opportunities for community engagement on 
 this topic will be announced in the coming weeks.</p><p dir="ltr">Those wis
 hing to provide comments regarding school climate and school safety may sig
 n up in advance using the District’s form for submitting public comment at 
 <a href="www.spps.org/boe">www.spps.org/boe</a> or by e-mailing or calling 
 the Board Secretary (sarah.dahlke@spps.org / 651-767-8149).</p><p dir="ltr"
 >Those who do not sign up in advance will still be allowed to provide comme
 nts. Individuals providing comments are asked to speak for a maximum of two
  minutes.</p><p dir="ltr">The meeting is open to all. The public may monito
 r the meeting via live stream at <a href="www.spps.org/boe.">www.spps.org/b
 oe.</a></p><br><br><p dir="ltr">February 23\, 2023</p><br><p dir="ltr"> Jim
  Vue<br> Chair\, Board of Education</p><p dir="ltr"> Independent School Dis
 trict No. 625</p><br> Saint Paul Public Schools
LAST-MODIFIED:20230223T193359Z
LOCATION:Washington Technology Magnet School\, 1495 Rice St\, St Paul\, MN 
 55117\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MTG | Special re: Listening Session on School Safety
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
