 &nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>PLEASE TAKE NOTICE\, that by action of the Boa
 rd of Education of Independent School District No. 625\,&nbsp\;pursuant to 
 Minnesota Statutes Section 13D.021&nbsp\;and the current state of emergency
  due to the COVID-19 pandemic\,&nbsp\;all future&nbsp\;meetings of the Boar
 d of Education&nbsp\;will be conducted via&nbsp\;a telephonic phone confere
 nce.&nbsp\;This includes the regular meeting of the Board of Education sche
 duled for Tuesday\, March 24\, 2020&nbsp\;and will continue until further n
 otice.&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><p>Consistent with current state and federa
 l pandemic guidance\, the undersigned has determined that\, due to the heal
 th pandemic and emergency declaration\, a meeting format allowing for open 
 in-person attendance is not practical or prudent.&nbsp\; As a result\, it i
 s unfeasible for at least one Board Member\, the Superintendent\, or Genera
 l Counsel to be physically present at the regular meeting location.&nbsp\; 
 It is also not feasible for members of the public to attend at the regular 
 meeting location.&nbsp\; The School District has set up a conference call t
 elephone number for members of the public who wish to monitor all future sc
 hool board meetings. Individuals wishing to monitor school board meetings s
 hould dial&nbsp\;1-651-728-5389&nbsp\;at 6:00 pm and enter the meeting code
 &nbsp\;129 614 310#.&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><br><p>For the March 24\, 202
 0 regular meeting of the Board of Education\, public comment will be accept
 ed by:&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><ol><li><p>&nbsp\;Leaving messages with the
  Board secretary at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:sarah.dahlke@spps.org">sarah.dahl
 ke@spps.org</a>&nbsp\;or 612-434-1105 that be&nbsp\;complied and distribute
 d to Board members\; and/or&nbsp\;</p></li></ol><br><p></p><br><ol><li><p>S
 ending&nbsp\;email statements to the&nbsp\;Board of Education&nbsp\;email (
 <a href="mailto:SB.Members@spps.org">SB.Members@spps.org</a>)&nbsp\;that wi
 ll be compiled and distributed to Board members.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p></li></ol
 ><br><p></p><br><p>Dated:&nbsp\;March 20\, 2020.&nbsp\;</p><br><p></p><br><
 p></p><br><p></p><br><p>Chair\, Board of Education&nbsp\;</p><br><p>Indepen
